# Apex Typography System

## Overview

This document defines the typography scale and usage guidelines for Apex, based on 2026 mobile-first best practices. The system prioritizes readability, prevents unnecessary text wrapping, and maintains visual hierarchy while minimizing wasted space.

## Core Principles

1. **Mobile-First**: All sizes are optimized for mobile screens first, with responsive scaling for larger devices.
2. **Accessibility**: Minimum 16px for body text and inputs to prevent iOS zoom and ensure readability.
3. **Consistency**: Use the defined type scale consistently across all pages and components.
4. **Efficiency**: Avoid oversized text that causes wrapping or wastes vertical space.
5. **Relative Units**: Use `rem`-based Tailwind classes (which use rem internally) for user resizing support.

## Type Scale

### Mobile-First Scale (Base: 16px = 1rem)

| Scale | Tailwind Class | Size (px) | Size (rem) | Use Case |
|-------|---------------|-----------|------------|----------|
| **xs** | `text-xs` | 12px | 0.75rem | Labels, captions, metadata, fine print |
| **sm** | `text-sm` | 14px | 0.875rem | Secondary text, helper text, dense UI only |
| **base** | `text-base` | 16px | 1rem | **Default body text, inputs, buttons** |
| **lg** | `text-lg` | 18px | 1.125rem | Emphasized body, card content, section descriptions |
| **xl** | `text-xl` | 20px | 1.25rem | Section titles, card titles, important content |
| **2xl** | `text-2xl` | 24px | 1.5rem | Page headers (mobile), large card titles |
| **3xl** | `text-3xl` | 30px | 1.875rem | Page headers (desktop), hero numbers |
| **4xl** | `text-4xl` | 36px | 2.25rem | Large hero numbers, dashboard stats |
| **5xl** | `text-5xl` | 48px | 3rem | Extra large hero numbers (sparingly) |

### Responsive Typography

For elements that need to scale between mobile and desktop:

```typescript
// Page headers
className="text-2xl md:text-3xl"  // 24px mobile → 30px desktop

// Section titles
className="text-xl md:text-2xl"    // 20px mobile → 24px desktop

// Body text (rarely needs scaling)
className="text-base md:text-lg"   // 16px mobile → 18px desktop (only if needed)
```

**Guideline**: Only scale up for page headers and major section titles. Most body text should remain at `text-base` (16px) on all screen sizes.

## Usage Guidelines by Element Type

### Page Headers
- **Mobile**: `text-xl` (20px) - `text-xl font-bold tracking-tight`
- **Desktop**: `text-2xl` (24px) - `text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight`
- **Example**: `<h1 className="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">Profile</h1>`
- **DO NOT** use `text-3xl` or larger for page headers - they cause unnecessary wrapping and waste space.

### Section Titles (Card Headers, Major Sections)
- **Standard**: `text-lg` (18px) - `text-lg font-semibold`
- **Responsive**: `text-lg md:text-xl` (18px → 20px) for very important sections only
- **Example**: `<h2 className="text-lg font-semibold text-apex-white">Rider Name</h2>`
- **DO NOT** use `text-xl` or larger on mobile - causes wrapping in cards.

### Card Titles (Within Cards)
- **Standard**: `text-base` (16px) - `text-base font-semibold`
- **Example**: `<h3 className="text-base font-semibold text-apex-white">Current Bike</h3>`
- **Alternative**: `text-sm font-semibold` (14px) for compact cards with limited space.

### Body Text (Default Content)
- **Standard**: `text-sm` (14px) - This is the default for general body text
- **Example**: `<p className="text-sm text-apex-white">Content here</p>`
- **MANDATORY for Inputs/Buttons**: `text-base` (16px) - Required for inputs and buttons to prevent iOS zoom
- **Why**: 16px prevents iOS zoom on input focus and ensures accessibility. General body text can be smaller.
- **DO NOT** use `text-xs` (12px) for primary body text - only for labels and metadata.

### Secondary Text (Muted, Helper, Metadata)
- **Standard**: `text-sm` (14px) - `text-sm text-apex-white/60`
- **Use Cases**: Helper text, descriptions, timestamps, metadata
- **Example**: `<p className="text-sm text-apex-white/60">Last updated 2 hours ago</p>`

### Labels (Form Labels, Uppercase Labels)
- **Standard**: `text-xs` (12px) - `text-xs text-apex-white/60 uppercase tracking-wide`
- **Use Cases**: Form field labels, section labels, metadata labels
- **Example**: `<label className="text-xs text-apex-white/60 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Email</label>`

### Telemetry & Numbers
- **Small Numbers**: `text-base font-mono` (16px) - `text-base font-mono text-apex-green`
- **Medium Numbers**: `text-lg font-mono` (18px) or `text-xl font-mono` (20px)
- **Large Stats**: `text-2xl font-mono` (24px) or `text-3xl font-mono` (30px)
- **Hero Numbers**: `text-4xl font-mono` (36px) or `text-5xl font-mono` (48px) - use sparingly
- **Example**: `<p className="text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white">1,234</p>`
- **Always use `font-mono`** for numbers and telemetry data.

### Buttons
- **Standard**: `text-base` (16px) - `text-base font-semibold`
- **Small Buttons**: `text-sm` (14px) - `text-sm font-semibold` (for compact UI only)
- **Large CTA**: `text-lg` (18px) - `text-lg font-semibold` (for primary actions only)
- **Example**: `<button className="text-base font-semibold text-apex-black bg-apex-green">Save</button>`
- **MANDATORY**: All input fields and buttons must be at least `text-base` (16px) to prevent iOS zoom.

### Input Fields
- **MANDATORY**: `text-base` (16px) minimum - `text-base` or `text-lg`
- **Example**: `<input className="text-base text-apex-white" />`
- **Why**: iOS Safari zooms in on inputs smaller than 16px, breaking UX.

### Empty States
- **Title**: `text-lg font-semibold` (18px)
- **Description**: `text-sm text-apex-white/60` (14px)
- **Example**: 
  ```tsx
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">No bikes yet</h2>
  <p className="text-base text-apex-white/60">Add your first machine...</p>
  ```

## Font Families

### Sans Serif (Default)
- **Usage**: Headers, body text, UI elements
- **Classes**: `font-sans` (default, no class needed) or `font-bold`, `font-semibold`
- **Headers**: `font-sans font-bold tracking-tight`
- **Body**: `font-sans` (default)

### Monospace (Telemetry)
- **Usage**: Numbers, telemetry data, code, technical values
- **Classes**: `font-mono`
- **Always combine with**: `text-apex-green` for telemetry values
- **Example**: `<span className="font-mono text-apex-green">45.2 km/h</span>`

## Line Height & Spacing

### Line Height
- Tailwind's default line heights are appropriate for most use cases.
- **Dense Text**: Use `leading-tight` for headers if needed.
- **Body Text**: Default line height (1.5) is optimal for readability.

### Letter Spacing
- **Headers**: `tracking-tight` for large headers (page titles)
- **Labels**: `tracking-wide` for uppercase labels
- **Body**: Default tracking (no class needed)

## Text Colors

### Primary Text
- **Default**: `text-apex-white` - Use for all primary content
- **Muted**: `text-apex-white/60` - Secondary text, descriptions
- **Subtle**: `text-apex-white/40` - Metadata, timestamps, helper text

### Accent Text
- **Telemetry**: `text-apex-green` - Always with `font-mono`
- **Errors**: `text-apex-red` - Error messages, warnings
- **Theme Colors**: Use theme colors for accents (via `useThemeColors` hook)

